1. HashMap without sort.
We define a hashMap. The key element denotes the members of the array. The value has 3 types:
value 1: the key appears once in the array
value 2: the key appears more than once in the array
value 0: the key has been used, this value is used to avoid duplicated pairs.
We use a for-loop to initial the hashMap. 
If k == 0, we just calculate the number which appears more than once in array.
if k != 0,  each number adds k and subtracts k, then using the result to match the map. 
```
class Solution {
    public int findPairs(int[] nums, int k) {
        if(k<0)return 0;
        Map<Integer,Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        for(int i = 0; i<nums.length; i++){
            if(map.containsKey(nums[i])){
                map.put(nums[i],2);
            }else{
                map.put(nums[i],1);
            }
        }
        int count = 0;
        if(k==0){
            for(int i = 0; i<nums.length; i++){
                if(map.containsKey(nums[i]) && map.get(nums[i]) > 1){
                    count++;
                    map.replace(nums[i],0);
                }
            }
            return count;
        }
        for(int i = 0; i<nums.length; i++){
            if(map.containsKey(nums[i] + k) && map.get(nums[i] + k) > 0 && map.get(nums[i]) > 0){
                count++;
            }
            if(map.containsKey(nums[i] - k) && map.get(nums[i] - k) > 0 && map.get(nums[i]) > 0){
                count++;
            }
            map.replace(nums[i],0);
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```

2. HashMap + Sort
This solution is similar to the first solution. 
We firstly sort the array, so we don't need to consider multiple situations(k==0 or k != 0 ; add or subtract). The sort reduces the complexity of this problem.
```
class Solution {
    public int findPairs(int[] nums, int k) {
        if(k < 0)return 0;
        Map<Integer, Boolean> map = new HashMap<>();
        int count = 0;
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        for(int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++){
            if(map.containsKey(nums[i]) && map.get(nums[i])){
                count++;
                map.replace(nums[i],false);
            }
            if(!map.containsKey(nums[i] + k)){
                map.put(nums[i] + k, true);
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```

