**TWO-POINTER APPROACH T(NLogN)**

1. The approach that I used here is similar to two-sum problem.
2. In two-sum we select two numbers that sums-up to k, whereas here we have to select two numbers with difference k.
3. I have used two pointers i & j, in two-sum the we start i from 0 and j from n-1, but here we'll start i from 0 and j from 1 because at this point the difference will be minimum b/w nums[i] and nums[j].

**CODE**
```
int findPairs(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.size();
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        int i=0, j=1, count=0;
        while(j<n){
            if(i==j) j++;
            if(j>n-1) break;
            if(nums[i]+k == nums[j]){
                count++;
                while(j<n and nums[i]+k == nums[j]) j++;
            }else if(nums[i]+k < nums[j]){
                i++;
            }else{
                j++;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
```

